parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel injector failure and leaks can cause gasoline odors, fuel leaks, and even vehicle fires, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Gasoline odors inside and outside the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the jack stands can cause the vehicle to fall, resulting in potential injury or death to the person underneath, as well as damage to the vehicle.
symptoms: The jack stands collapse or fail
causing the vehicle to fall or crash to the ground
potentially trapping or crushing the person underneath.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective fuel injectors can cause a fuel rich condition, leading to poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially even engine damage or failure. Additionally, the fuel odor and leakage can pose a fire hazard.
symptoms: sudden appearance of issues after normal operation.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Recall Notification and Repair
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to notify owners of the recall and perform the necessary repairs can lead to continued operation of the vehicle with a defective component, potentially causing safety issues and engine damage.
symptoms: continued operation of vehicle with defective component.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, especially if the vehicle is traveling at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly accelerates without pressing the accelerator pedal
the vehicle surges forward without warning
the vehicle takes off without application of the accelerator.
